                            <comment id="15858450" author="william.droste@arris.com" created="Wed, 8 Feb 2017 19:40:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Excellent thanks for the quick reply, next time I&apos;ll check the latest must of been on a tag.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;IMHO I would not call &apos;flush&apos; there because the underlying OutputStream should finish the stream based on the close. If they correctly abide by the spec.. It should not be required however if the design decision here is to be conservative I totally understand. I often flush and close at the application layer to be sure.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
